Vladimir Putin has ordered Russia's army to to observe a 36-hour ceasefire in Ukraine in what is a major turning point in the conflict between the two countries. A statement read: "Taking into account the appeal of His Holiness Patriarch Kirill, I instruct the Minister of Defence of the Russian Federation to introduce from 12:00 on January 6 to 24:00 on January 7 a ceasefire along the entire line of combat contact of the parties in Ukraine. Based on the fact that a large number of citizens professing Orthodoxy live in the combat areas, we call on the Ukrainian side to declare a cease-fire and give them the opportunity to attend services on Christmas Eve, as well as on the Day of the Nativity of Christ." FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...  